Content:
@bobo38 - Most people complain about not having enough I/O, so I'm excited for people who think they can do something with the much more limited 12 or 20 I/O count. 

I think of 12 I/O as 2 power, 8 bit bidir bus and 2 control while 20 I/O is 16 bit bidir.

Packaging is about 1-2 cents a pin + some fixed cost (around ~10-15 cents), so with something like 12 I/O we might be able to get packaging down to $0.50 each.
